snippet.textDisplay: Words are helpless rather they have become extincted to explain the performance and this peerless mystic creation. Wisdom itself is wondering how great mysticism dipped in classical patterns depicted in the voice of emerging vocal Javed Bashir has made it eternal and unprecedented. The lilt, flow in turning voice, vocal turbulence with harmony and beautifying therewith the delivery of tune in classical ups and down has been so innovative in each line one wonders how Coke Studio, the Music Director Mr. Zaidi has made it possible. It is an emerging magic and spreading light exposing truth of the great eminence of Hazrat Ali (Razi Allah o Ta'aala Unho). Javed Bashir ! May you live long, the whole team is cordially appreciated in this creation. Its effect remains and makes the heart tossing restlessly to help listen to it many, many times. Awesome you are, the whole team.Great work, so professional, so profound.

snippet.textDisplay:
In post Rohail Hyatt era, only two composers have shown promise, Jaffer Zaidi and Shuja Haider.
Well done, CS though I still wish Rohail was directing all this and adding his magical touch. He would have made this into a masterpiece.
Ali Azmat and Javed Bashir 's combo is a good one. The song/qawwali loses touch at a couple of points e.g at 5:29, but overall it is very good.
